The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Sehwag confirmed as deputy
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Sehwag confirmed as deputy
            OUR CORRESPONDENT                      
	Nagpur: Virender Sehwag was on Friday appointed vice-captain of the Indian team for the upcoming series against England.         
	Sehwag, who will take up his new role with immediate effect, will be Mahendra Singh Dhonis deputy in both one-dayers and Tests, as first reported by The Telegraph on Thursday.         
	India are to play seven ODIs and two Tests against England. The first one-dayer is in Rajkot on November 14.         
	England have already arrived in Mumbai and will play two warm-up one-day games ahead of the series.         
	Sehwag was the vice-captain when India played the Test series against Sri Lanka in July-August.                                                                                                                          
